TY  - JOUR
T1  - Social Undermining in the Workplace
AU  - Duffy, Michelle K.
AU  - Ganster, Daniel C.
AU  - Pagon, Milan
Y1  - 2002/04/01
PY  - 2002
DA  - 2002/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/3069350
DO  - 10.5465/3069350
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 331
EP  - 351
VL  - 45
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - An interactive model of social undermining and social support in the workplace was developed and tested among police officers in the Republic of Slovenia. As predicted, social undermining was significantly associated with employee outcomes, in most cases more strongly than was social support. High levels of undermining and support from the same source were associated with negative outcomes. However, support from one source appeared to only modestly attenuate the negative effects of social undermining from another source.
AB  - An interactive model of social undermining and social support in the workplace was developed and tested among police officers in the Republic of Slovenia. As predicted, social undermining was significantly associated with employee outcomes, in most cases more strongly than was social support. High levels of undermining and support from the same source were associated with negative outcomes. However, support from one source appeared to only modestly attenuate the negative effects of social undermining from another source.
